     9	 * and the copied state. This is intentional and safe because:
    10	 * 1. Fork cache is read-only relative to the forked blockchain state at a specific block
    11	 * 2. Sharing the cache improves performance by preventing duplicate remote fetches
    12	 * 3. It enables persistent caching of fork data across VM instances
